{
  "texts": [
    "This mechanism necessitates human evaluation and confirmation.",
    "Only reports that pass this confirmation or have been corrected by doctors can proceed to the next step.",
    "This guard mechanism is open to be optimized and updated to enhance efficiency.",
    "Although the BLIP model can be used for further QA tasks, it requires a large amount of reliable QA training data and significant computational resources, which makes the training and continuous optimization challenging (see Supplementary Table 5).",
    "To enable QA without the need for fine-tuning and to facilitate interactive interpretation of the generated reports, we incorporated the advanced open-source large language model, Llama 2 9 in the second step as the GPT module to enable QA."
  ]
}